I found the issue! Looking at the CSS styles for the modal, I can see that the `.modal-overlay` class has:

```css
.modal-overlay {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);  /* This is correct - 50% opacity */
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  z-index: var(--z-index-modal);
  padding: var(--spacing-lg);
}
```

The modal overlay CSS looks correct with `rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5)` which should provide a semi-transparent overlay. However, the issue might be related to how the dark mode is affecting the background or there could be an issue with the component itself. Let me check if there are any other CSS files that might be overriding these styles:
